{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1908,"text":"(Video) Announcer: 10 seconds."},{"time":7000,"text":"Five, four, three, two, one."},{"time":11904,"text":"Official top."},{"time":13245,"text":"Plus one, two, three, four, five"},{"time":18078,"text":"six, seven, eight, nine, ten."},{"time":26153,"text":"Guillaume Néry, France."},{"time":28201,"text":"Constant weight, 123 meters,"},{"time":31865,"text":"three minutes and 25 seconds."},{"time":34147,"text":"National record attempt."},{"time":67834,"text":"70 meters."},{"time":80056,"text":"[123 meters]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":129166,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":132148,"text":"(Video) Judge: White card.\nGuillaume Néry! National record!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":137745,"text":"Guillaume Néry: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139015,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142840,"text":"Thank you very much,\nthanks for the warm welcome."},{"time":145418,"text":"That dive you just watched is a journey --"},{"time":148646,"text":"a journey between two breaths."},{"time":151367,"text":"A journey that takes place\nbetween two breaths --"},{"time":153686,"text":"the last one before diving into the water,"},{"time":155964,"text":"and the first one,\ncoming back to the surface."},{"time":159394,"text":"That dive is a journey\nto the very limits of human possibility,"},{"time":163792,"text":"a journey into the unknown."},{"time":166315,"text":"But it's also, and above all,\nan inner journey,"},{"time":169870,"text":"where a number of things happen,"},{"time":172288,"text":"physiologically as well as mentally."},{"time":174641,"text":"And that's why I'm here today,"},{"time":176681,"text":"to share my journey with you\nand to take you along with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180038,"text":"So, we start with the last breath."},{"time":183987,"text":"(Breathing in)"},{"time":197279,"text":"(Breathing out)"},{"time":199143,"text":"As you noticed, that last breath\nin is slow, deep and intense."},{"time":203610,"text":"It ends with a special technique\ncalled the carp,"},{"time":206190,"text":"which allows me to store one to two\nextra liters of air in my lungs"},{"time":209855,"text":"by compressing it."},{"time":211992,"text":"When I leave the surface,\nI have about 10 liters of air in my lungs."},{"time":217539,"text":"As soon as I leave the surface\nthe first mechanism kicks in:"},{"time":221084,"text":"the diving reflex."},{"time":222544,"text":"The first thing the diving reflex does\nis make your heart rate drop."},{"time":227452,"text":"My heart beat will drop\nfrom about 60-70 per minute"},{"time":230309,"text":"to about 30-40 beats per minute"},{"time":232113,"text":"in a matter of seconds;\nalmost immediately."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235058,"text":"Next, the diving reflex causes\nperipheral vasoconstriction,"},{"time":238171,"text":"which means that the blood flow\nwill leave the body's extremities"},{"time":242365,"text":"to feed the most important organs:"},{"time":246382,"text":"the lungs, the heart and the brain."},{"time":250602,"text":"This mechanism is innate."},{"time":254110,"text":"I cannot control it."},{"time":255550,"text":"If you go underwater,\neven if you've never done it before,"},{"time":258366,"text":"you'll experience the exact same effects."},{"time":260735,"text":"All human beings\nshare this characteristic."},{"time":264382,"text":"And what's extraordinary"},{"time":266332,"text":"is that we share this instinct\nwith marine mammals --"},{"time":269873,"text":"all marine mammals:\ndolphins, whales, sea lions, etc."},{"time":273555,"text":"When they dive deep into the ocean,\nthese mechanisms become activated,"},{"time":278175,"text":"but to a greater extent."},{"time":279532,"text":"And, of course, it works\nmuch better for them."},{"time":283970,"text":"It's absolutely fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285388,"text":"Right as I leave the surface,"},{"time":286838,"text":"nature gives me a push\nin the right direction,"},{"time":289171,"text":"allowing me to descend with confidence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291587,"text":"So as I dive deeper into the blue,"},{"time":293627,"text":"the pressure slowly starts\nto squeeze my lungs."},{"time":298338,"text":"And since it's the amount of air\nin my lungs that makes me float,"},{"time":301613,"text":"the farther down I go,\nthe more pressure there is on my lungs,"},{"time":304565,"text":"the less air they contain\nand the easier it is for my body to fall."},{"time":308192,"text":"And at one point,\naround 35 or 40 meters down,"},{"time":311019,"text":"I don't even need to swim."},{"time":314468,"text":"My body is dense and heavy enough\nto fall into the depths by itself,"},{"time":319263,"text":"and I enter what's called\nthe free fall phase."},{"time":321882,"text":"The free fall phase\nis the best part of the dive."},{"time":324628,"text":"It's the reason I still dive."},{"time":326530,"text":"Because it feels like\nyou're being pulled down"},{"time":331401,"text":"and you don't need to do anything."},{"time":333122,"text":"I can go from 35 meters to 123 meters\nwithout making a single movement."},{"time":337040,"text":"I let myself be pulled by the depths,"},{"time":339006,"text":"and it feels like I'm flying underwater."},{"time":340968,"text":"It's truly an amazing feeling --\nan extraordinary feeling of freedom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344975,"text":"And so I slowly continue\nsliding to the bottom."},{"time":347982,"text":"40 meters down,"},{"time":349286,"text":"50 meters down,"},{"time":350607,"text":"and between 50 and 60 meters,\na second physiological response kicks in."},{"time":355702,"text":"My lungs reach residual volume,"},{"time":358242,"text":"below which they're not supposed\nto be compressed, in theory."},{"time":363205,"text":"And this second response\nis called blood shift,"},{"time":366755,"text":"or \"pulmonary erection\" in French."},{"time":370236,"text":"I prefer \"blood shift.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":371569,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":372750,"text":"So blood shift -- how does it work?"},{"time":375519,"text":"The capillaries in the lungs\nbecome engorged with blood --"},{"time":380117,"text":"which is caused by the suction --"},{"time":381734,"text":"so the lungs can harden"},{"time":383469,"text":"and protect the whole chest cavity\nfrom being crushed."},{"time":386165,"text":"It prevents the two walls\nof the lungs from collapsing,"},{"time":390092,"text":"from sticking together and caving in."},{"time":392078,"text":"Thanks to this phenomenon,\nwhich we also share with marine mammals,"},{"time":395991,"text":"I'm able to continue with my dive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397718,"text":"60, 70 meters down,\nI keep falling, faster and faster,"},{"time":401318,"text":"because the pressure is crushing\nmy body more and more."},{"time":404254,"text":"Below 80 meters,"},{"time":406355,"text":"the pressure becomes a lot stronger,"},{"time":408394,"text":"and I start to feel it physically."},{"time":410489,"text":"I really start to feel the suffocation."},{"time":412518,"text":"You can see what it looks like --\nnot pretty at all."},{"time":415002,"text":"The diaphragm is completely collapsed,\nthe rib cage is squeezed in,"},{"time":419824,"text":"and mentally, there is something\ngoing on as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422331,"text":"You may be thinking,\n\"This doesn't look enjoyable."},{"time":425122,"text":"How do you do it?\""},{"time":426445,"text":"If I relied on my earthly reflexes --"},{"time":428270,"text":"what do we do above water\nwhen there's a problem?"},{"time":431757,"text":"We resist, we go against it."},{"time":433990,"text":"We fight."},{"time":435357,"text":"Underwater, that doesn't work."},{"time":436913,"text":"If you try that underwater,\nyou might tear your lungs,"},{"time":439529,"text":"spit up blood, develop an edema"},{"time":441119,"text":"and you'll have to stop diving\nfor a good amount of time."},{"time":444278,"text":"So what you need to do, mentally,\nis to tell yourself"},{"time":447476,"text":"that nature and the elements\nare stronger than you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450270,"text":"And so I let the water crush me."},{"time":452920,"text":"I accept the pressure and go with it."},{"time":456481,"text":"At this point, my body\nreceives this information,"},{"time":458849,"text":"and my lungs start relaxing."},{"time":460731,"text":"I relinquish all control,\nand relax completely."},{"time":463898,"text":"The pressure starts crushing me,\nand it doesn't feel bad at all."},{"time":467772,"text":"I even feel like\nI'm in a cocoon, protected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471106,"text":"And the dive continues."},{"time":473702,"text":"80, 85 meters down,"},{"time":475424,"text":"90,"},{"time":476667,"text":"100."},{"time":477874,"text":"100 meters -- the magic number."},{"time":481024,"text":"In every sport, it's a magic number."},{"time":482910,"text":"For swimmers and athletes\nand also for us, free divers,"},{"time":485764,"text":"it's a number everyone dreams of."},{"time":487434,"text":"Everyone wishes one day\nto be able to get to 100 meters."},{"time":490856,"text":"And it's a symbolic number for us,"},{"time":492665,"text":"because in the 1970s,\ndoctors and physiologists did their math,"},{"time":496556,"text":"and predicted that the human body\nwould not be able to go below 100 meters."},{"time":501889,"text":"Below that, they said,\nthe human body would implode."},{"time":504769,"text":"And then the Frenchman, Jacques Mayol --"},{"time":506905,"text":"you all know him as the hero\nin \"The Big Blue\" --"},{"time":509222,"text":"came along and dived down to 100 meters."},{"time":512499,"text":"He even reached 105 meters."},{"time":514088,"text":"At that time, he was doing \"no limits.\""},{"time":516008,"text":"He'd use weights to descend faster\nand come back up with a balloon,"},{"time":519381,"text":"just like in the movie."},{"time":520577,"text":"Today, we go down 200 meters\nin no limit free diving."},{"time":523179,"text":"I can do 123 meters\nby simply using muscle strength."},{"time":526059,"text":"And in a way, it's all thanks to him,\nbecause he challenged known facts,"},{"time":529814,"text":"and with a sweep of his hand,\ngot rid of the theoretical beliefs"},{"time":534205,"text":"and all the mental limits\nthat we like to impose on ourselves."},{"time":537630,"text":"He showed us that the human body\nhas an infinite ability to adapt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541270,"text":"So I carry on with my dive."},{"time":543013,"text":"105, 110, 115."},{"time":545171,"text":"The bottom is getting closer."},{"time":546965,"text":"120,"},{"time":548465,"text":"123 meters."},{"time":549679,"text":"I'm at the bottom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550982,"text":"And now, I'd like to ask you to join me\nand put yourself in my place."},{"time":554616,"text":"Close your eyes."},{"time":556752,"text":"Imagine you get to 123 meters."},{"time":561541,"text":"The surface is far, far away."},{"time":564720,"text":"You're alone."},{"time":567864,"text":"There's hardly any light."},{"time":570324,"text":"It's cold --"},{"time":571603,"text":"freezing cold."},{"time":572984,"text":"The pressure is crushing you completely --"},{"time":575061,"text":"13 times stronger than on the surface."},{"time":578214,"text":"And I know what you're thinking:"},{"time":580147,"text":"\"This is horrible."},{"time":582120,"text":"What the hell am I doing here?"},{"time":584000,"text":"He's insane.\""},{"time":586484,"text":"But no."},{"time":588031,"text":"That's not what I think\nwhen I'm down there."},{"time":590315,"text":"When I'm at the bottom, I feel good."},{"time":592064,"text":"I get this extraordinary\nfeeling of well-being."},{"time":594345,"text":"Maybe it's because I've completely\nreleased all tensions"},{"time":597258,"text":"and let myself go."},{"time":599003,"text":"I feel great, without the need to breathe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605238,"text":"Although, you'd agree,\nI should be worried."},{"time":609999,"text":"I feel like a tiny dot,\na little drop of water,"},{"time":612346,"text":"floating in the middle of the ocean."},{"time":614220,"text":"And each time, I picture the same image."},{"time":617736,"text":"[The Pale Blue Dot]"},{"time":620473,"text":"It's that small dot\nthe arrow is pointing to."},{"time":622951,"text":"Do you know what it is?"},{"time":625480,"text":"It's planet Earth."},{"time":627478,"text":"Planet Earth, photographed\nby the Voyager probe,"},{"time":630163,"text":"from 4 billion kilometers away."},{"time":632339,"text":"And it shows that our home\nis that small dot over there,"},{"time":636459,"text":"floating in the middle of nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638126,"text":"That's how I feel"},{"time":640071,"text":"when I'm at the bottom, at 123 meters."},{"time":642246,"text":"I feel like a small dot,"},{"time":643985,"text":"a speck of dust, stardust,"},{"time":646564,"text":"floating in the middle of the cosmos,"},{"time":648803,"text":"in the middle of nothing,\nin the immensity of space."},{"time":651271,"text":"It's a fascinating sensation,"},{"time":652736,"text":"because when I look up, down,\nleft, right, in front, behind,"},{"time":656815,"text":"I see the same thing:\nthe infinite deep blue."},{"time":660030,"text":"Nowhere else on Earth\nyou can experience this --"},{"time":663070,"text":"looking all around you,\nand seeing the same thing."},{"time":666657,"text":"It's extraordinary."},{"time":668562,"text":"And at that moment,"},{"time":670026,"text":"I still get that feeling each time,\nbuilding up inside of me --"},{"time":673051,"text":"the feeling of humility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676875,"text":"Looking at this picture,\nI feel very humble --"},{"time":679805,"text":"just like when I'm all the way\ndown at the bottom --"},{"time":682360,"text":"because I'm nothing,"},{"time":683661,"text":"I'm a little speck of nothingness\nlost in all of time and space."},{"time":687652,"text":"And it still is absolutely fascinating."},{"time":690660,"text":"I decide to go back to the surface,\nbecause this is not where I belong."},{"time":694487,"text":"I belong up there, on the surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696740,"text":"So I start heading back up."},{"time":700018,"text":"I get something of a shock"},{"time":704293,"text":"at the very moment when I decide to go up."},{"time":706780,"text":"First, because it takes a huge effort\nto tear yourself away from the bottom."},{"time":710711,"text":"It pulled you down on the way in,"},{"time":713215,"text":"and will do the same on the way up."},{"time":715122,"text":"You have to swim twice as hard."},{"time":718480,"text":"Then, I'm hit with another\nphenomenon known as narcosis."},{"time":721522,"text":"I don't know if you've heard of that."},{"time":723318,"text":"It's called nitrogen narcosis."},{"time":725469,"text":"It's something that happens\nto scuba divers,"},{"time":727630,"text":"but it can happen to free divers."},{"time":729273,"text":"It's caused by nitrogen\ndissolving in the blood,"},{"time":732826,"text":"which causes confusion"},{"time":734744,"text":"between the conscious\nand unconscious mind."},{"time":738212,"text":"A flurry of thoughts goes spinning\nthrough your head."},{"time":742443,"text":"You can't control them,\nand you shouldn't try to --"},{"time":745463,"text":"you have to let it happen."},{"time":747071,"text":"The more you try to control it,\nthe harder it is to manage."},{"time":751223,"text":"Then, a third thing happens:"},{"time":752715,"text":"the desire to breathe."},{"time":754008,"text":"I'm not a fish, I'm a human being,"},{"time":756342,"text":"and the desire to breathe\nreminds me of that fact."},{"time":759887,"text":"Around 60, 70 meters,"},{"time":763551,"text":"you start to feel the need to breathe."},{"time":767650,"text":"And with everything else that's going on,"},{"time":770110,"text":"you can very easily lose your ground"},{"time":773071,"text":"and start to panic."},{"time":775871,"text":"When that happens, you think,\n\"Where's the surface?"},{"time":778316,"text":"I want to go up. I want to breathe now.\""},{"time":780275,"text":"You should not do that."},{"time":781931,"text":"Never look up to the surface --"},{"time":783789,"text":"not with your eyes, or your mind."},{"time":787161,"text":"You should never\npicture yourself up there."},{"time":789914,"text":"You have to stay in the present."},{"time":791576,"text":"I look at the rope right in front of me,\nleading me back to the surface."},{"time":796834,"text":"And I focus on that,\non the present moment."},{"time":799829,"text":"Because if I think\nabout the surface, I panic."},{"time":802029,"text":"And if I panic, it's over."},{"time":804925,"text":"Time goes faster this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807160,"text":"And at 30 meters: deliverance."},{"time":809279,"text":"I'm not alone any more."},{"time":810707,"text":"The safety divers,\nmy guardian angels, join me."},{"time":814130,"text":"They leave the surface,\nwe meet at 30 meters,"},{"time":816477,"text":"and they escort me\nfor the final few meters,"},{"time":818655,"text":"where potential problems could arise."},{"time":821881,"text":"Every time I see them, I think to myself,"},{"time":825253,"text":"\"It's thanks to you.\""},{"time":826865,"text":"It's thanks to them,\nmy team, that I'm here."},{"time":828985,"text":"It brings back the sense of humility."},{"time":831611,"text":"Without my team, without all\nthe people around me,"},{"time":835080,"text":"the adventure into the deep\nwould be impossible."},{"time":837459,"text":"A journey into the deep\nis above all a group effort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841359,"text":"So I'm happy to finish\nmy journey with them,"},{"time":843641,"text":"because I wouldn't be here\nif it weren't for them."},{"time":846159,"text":"20 meters, 10 meters,"},{"time":847774,"text":"my lungs slowly return\nto their normal volume."},{"time":850045,"text":"Buoyancy pushes me up to the surface."},{"time":852416,"text":"Five meters below the surface,\nI start to breathe out,"},{"time":855988,"text":"so that as soon as I get\nto the surface all I do is breathe in."},{"time":859277,"text":"And so I arrive at the surface."},{"time":861544,"text":"(Breathing in)"},{"time":867667,"text":"Air floods into my lungs."},{"time":869685,"text":"It's like being born again, a relief."},{"time":872896,"text":"It feels good."},{"time":874075,"text":"Though the journey was extraordinary,"},{"time":875965,"text":"I do need to feel those small\noxygen molecules fueling my body."},{"time":880385,"text":"It's an extraordinary sensation,\nbut at the same time it's traumatizing."},{"time":883994,"text":"It's a shock to the system,\nas you can you imagine."},{"time":886415,"text":"I go from complete darkness\nto the light of day,"},{"time":889212,"text":"from the near-silence of the depths\nto the commotion up top."},{"time":894388,"text":"In terms of touch, I go from the soft,\nvelvety feeling of the water,"},{"time":898945,"text":"to air rubbing across my face."},{"time":901271,"text":"In terms of smell,"},{"time":904272,"text":"there is air rushing into my lungs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906932,"text":"And in return, my lungs open up."},{"time":909368,"text":"They were completely squashed\njust 90 seconds ago,"},{"time":911935,"text":"and now, they've opened up again."},{"time":913647,"text":"So all of this affects\nquite a lot of things."},{"time":917507,"text":"I need a few seconds to come back,"},{"time":919851,"text":"and to feel \"all there\" again."},{"time":921454,"text":"But that needs to happen quickly,"},{"time":923060,"text":"because the judges are there\nto verify my performance;"},{"time":926196,"text":"I need to show them\nI'm in perfect physical condition."},{"time":928805,"text":"You saw in the video,\nI was doing a so-called exit protocol."},{"time":931681,"text":"Once at the surface, I have 15 seconds\nto take off my nose clip,"},{"time":936684,"text":"give this signal and say\n(English) \"I am OK.\""},{"time":939989,"text":"Plus, you need to be bilingual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941511,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":942977,"text":"On top of everything --"},{"time":944167,"text":"that's not very nice."},{"time":946897,"text":"Once the protocol is completed,\nthe judges show me a white card,"},{"time":950572,"text":"and that's when the joy starts."},{"time":952501,"text":"I can finally celebrate\nwhat has just happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955976,"text":"So, the journey I've just described to you"},{"time":958278,"text":"is a more extreme version of free diving."},{"time":961921,"text":"Luckily, it's far from just that."},{"time":964136,"text":"For the past few years,"},{"time":965367,"text":"I've been trying to show\nanother side of free diving,"},{"time":968078,"text":"because the media mainly talks\nabout competitions and records."},{"time":971209,"text":"But free diving is more than just that."},{"time":973114,"text":"It's about being at ease in the water."},{"time":975066,"text":"It's extremely beautiful,\nvery poetic and artistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978074,"text":"So my wife and I decided to film it"},{"time":980162,"text":"and try to show another side of it,"},{"time":983284,"text":"mostly to make people want\nto go into the water."},{"time":986089,"text":"Let me show you some images\nto finish my story."},{"time":991854,"text":"It's a mix of beautiful underwater photos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994060,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":995236,"text":"I'd like you to know that if one day\nyou try to stop breathing,"},{"time":1000319,"text":"you'll realize that\nwhen you stop breathing,"},{"time":1002639,"text":"you stop thinking, too."},{"time":1005355,"text":"It calms your mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007934,"text":"Today, in the 21st century,\nwe're under so much pressure."},{"time":1011244,"text":"Our minds are overworked,\nwe think at a million miles an hour,"},{"time":1014295,"text":"we're always stressed."},{"time":1016199,"text":"Being able to free dive\nlets you, just for a moment,"},{"time":1019227,"text":"relax your mind."},{"time":1021362,"text":"Holding your breath underwater"},{"time":1023378,"text":"means giving yourself the chance\nto experience weightlessness."},{"time":1027398,"text":"It means being underwater, floating,"},{"time":1030376,"text":"with your body completely relaxed,\nletting go of all your tensions."},{"time":1034223,"text":"This is our plight in the 21st century:"},{"time":1036126,"text":"our backs hurt, our necks hurt,\neverything hurts,"},{"time":1038467,"text":"because we're stressed\nand tense all the time."},{"time":1040700,"text":"But when you're in the water,"},{"time":1042153,"text":"you let yourself float,\nas if you were in space."},{"time":1045151,"text":"You let yourself go completely."},{"time":1046859,"text":"It's an extraordinary feeling."},{"time":1048376,"text":"You can finally get in touch\nwith your body, mind and spirit."},{"time":1054476,"text":"Everything feels better, all at once."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1057952,"text":"Learning how to free dive is also\nabout learning to breathe correctly."},{"time":1062718,"text":"We breathe with our first breath\nat birth, up until our last one."},{"time":1067200,"text":"Breathing gives rhythm to our lives."},{"time":1070778,"text":"Learning how to breathe better\nis learning how to live better."},{"time":1074746,"text":"Holding your breath in the sea,\nnot necessarily at 100 meters,"},{"time":1077905,"text":"but maybe at two or three,"},{"time":1079204,"text":"putting on your goggles,\na pair of flippers,"},{"time":1081294,"text":"means you can go see another world,"},{"time":1083014,"text":"another universe, completely magical."},{"time":1085096,"text":"You can see little fish, seaweed,\nthe flora and fauna,"},{"time":1088525,"text":"you can watch it all discreetly,"},{"time":1090867,"text":"sliding underwater, looking around,\nand coming back to the surface,"},{"time":1094177,"text":"leaving no trace."},{"time":1096096,"text":"It's an amazing feeling\nto become one with nature like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101219,"text":"And if I may say one more thing,"},{"time":1104509,"text":"holding your breath, being in the water,\nfinding this underwater world --"},{"time":1109700,"text":"it's all about connecting with yourself."},{"time":1111693,"text":"You heard me talk a lot\nabout the body's memory"},{"time":1116621,"text":"that dates back millions of years,\nto our marine origins."},{"time":1119546,"text":"The day you get back into the water,"},{"time":1122236,"text":"when you hold your breath\nfor a few seconds,"},{"time":1124751,"text":"you will reconnect with those origins."},{"time":1128243,"text":"And I guarantee"},{"time":1129786,"text":"it's absolute magic."},{"time":1131151,"text":"I encourage you to try it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1132628,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1133818,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}